---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Hungary Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/hungary/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Austria for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/austria' },
  { title: 'Croatia for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/croatia' },
  { title: 'Czech Republic for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/czech-republic' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'hungaryFit', header: 'Hungary Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€240-340/mo', hungaryFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€290-400/mo', hungaryFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€220-310/mo', hungaryFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'AXA Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€200-290/mo', hungaryFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Hungarian TAJ (Public)', entryAge: 'No limit', renewal: 'N/A', monthlyFrom: 'HUF 9,000', hungaryFit: 'For Residents' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: '€220-340', annual: '€2,640-4,080' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: '€300-450', annual: '€3,600-5,400' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: '€400-600', annual: '€4,800-7,200' },
  { category: 'Hungarian Public (TAJ)', monthly: 'HUF 9,000 (~€24)', annual: 'HUF 108,000 (~€290)' },
  { category: 'Hungarian Private Top-up', monthly: 'HUF 20,000-50,000', annual: 'HUF 240,000-600,000' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Hungary 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Hungary. Budapest healthcare, thermal spas, EU residence, and affordable coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Hungary"
  subheadline="Hungary offers excellent value: rich culture, thermal spas, affordable living, and EU membership—with both public and private healthcare options."
  heroImage="/images/countries/hungary-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Hungary</h2>
  <p>
    Hungary offers exceptional value for retirees: low cost of living, rich culture, thermal spas famous for health benefits, and central European location. Budapest is one of Europe's most beautiful capitals, with surprisingly good healthcare at affordable prices.
  </p>

  <p>
    Budapest draws most expats with its stunning architecture, thermal baths, and cultural offerings. Lake Balaton provides a more relaxed setting. Eger and Pécs offer smaller city charm. The countryside provides extremely affordable living for those seeking quiet.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Good quality; improving rapidly</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Hungarian (unique; English in Budapest)</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> €1,200-2,000/month; one of EU's lowest</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Continental; hot summers, cold winters</li>
      <li><strong>EU Status:</strong> Full EU member; Schengen zone</li>
      <li><strong>Thermal Spas:</strong> Famous for therapeutic treatments</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Hungary's Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Hungary has a social health insurance system (TAJ). Public healthcare is funded through contributions and taxes. Quality has improved significantly, though public hospitals can be crowded. Private healthcare is growing rapidly in Budapest with modern facilities.
  </p>

  <p>
    Budapest has excellent private clinics and hospitals. Dental tourism is huge—many Europeans visit for affordable, quality dental work. Medical tourism for various procedures is common. Pharmacies are well-stocked and affordable.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Language Consideration</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Hungarian is one of Europe's most difficult languages and is unrelated to neighboring languages. In Budapest, especially at private clinics, English is common. Outside Budapest, German may be more useful than English. Consider language support when choosing healthcare providers.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Hungary offers standard EU pathways for retirees:
  </p>

  <h3>Residence Permit (Financially Independent)</h3>
  <p>
    For non-EU nationals with proof of income (typically €1,000-1,500/month), accommodation, and comprehensive health insurance. Valid 1 year, renewable. After 5 years, apply for permanent residence.
  </p>

  <h3>EU Citizens</h3>
  <p>
    Free movement rights. Register after 90 days with proof of income/resources and health insurance. Once registered, can access Hungarian healthcare system.
  </p>

  <h3>Investor Program (Terminated)</h3>
  <p>
    Hungary's golden visa program has been terminated. Current pathways are standard residence permits for those with income/insurance.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Hungary:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Residence permit:</strong> Comprehensive health insurance required</li>
    <li><strong>EU citizens:</strong> EHIC initially; then register for Hungarian TAJ</li>
    <li><strong>TAJ enrollment:</strong> Available to residents; monthly contribution ~HUF 9,000</li>
    <li><strong>Private option:</strong> Many choose private insurance for faster, better care</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Hungary</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      Start with international insurance for residence permit. Once established, you can enroll in TAJ (very affordable). Many expats maintain private/international coverage for quality care and travel. Budapest private healthcare is excellent and reasonably priced.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Hungary, these providers offer strong coverage at competitive prices:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Hungary</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Good Central European network, competitive pricing</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), strong for British expats</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Excellent DACH/Central Europe coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Hungarian TAJ:</strong> Remarkably cheap once resident (~€24/month)</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage and pricing from providers that accept seniors for Hungary.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Hungary are among the lowest in the EU:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>TAJ enrollment:</strong> €24/month is incredibly cheap for EU healthcare access</li>
    <li><strong>Private direct pay:</strong> Budapest private care is affordable; pay cash for routine</li>
    <li><strong>Higher deductibles:</strong> €3,000+ deductible saves significantly</li>
    <li><strong>Hungary exclusion:</strong> If using TAJ, exclude Hungary from international policy</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: American Retiree, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $2,000/month pension. Moving to Budapest for cultural life and value.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global for residence permit. After establishing, enroll in TAJ. Keep Cigna for US visits.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Initially ~€300/month. After TAJ: ~€24/month TAJ + Cigna ~€200/month (Hungary excluded).</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: British Couple, Both 72</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Post-Brexit, retiring to Lake Balaton. £2,000/month combined.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global initially. Enroll in TAJ after residence. BUPA for UK and travel.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Initially ~€700/month combined. After TAJ: ~€50 TAJ + €450 reduced BUPA.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Austrian EU Citizen, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Retiring from Vienna to cheaper Budapest. Austrian pension €1,600/month.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Register, enroll in TAJ. Add private Hungarian plan for better care.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> TAJ ~€24/month + private top-up ~€100/month. Excellent coverage, very affordable.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Budapest really that affordable?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes. A comfortable retirement in Budapest costs €1,500-2,000/month including rent. Outside Budapest, €1,200/month is possible. Restaurant meals cost €5-10. Public transport is excellent and cheap. Utilities and groceries are significantly lower than Western Europe.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What about the thermal spas?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Hungary has over 1,000 natural hot springs, many with therapeutic properties. Budapest's famous baths (Széchenyi, Gellért) are cultural institutions. Many seniors use thermal treatments for arthritis, joint problems, and general wellness. Some insurance covers medically prescribed treatments.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How difficult is Hungarian?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Very difficult. Hungarian is a Finno-Ugric language unrelated to surrounding Slavic and Germanic languages. Most expats learn basic phrases but rely on English (common in Budapest) or German (useful elsewhere). Healthcare providers in private clinics typically speak English.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How cold are Hungarian winters?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Cold but manageable. Budapest winters average -2 to 5°C with some sub-zero periods. Snow is common. Buildings are well-heated. Summers are hot (30-35°C). If you dislike cold, consider that Hungary has continental climate with distinct seasons.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers that specialize in senior expat coverage for Hungary.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Hungarian authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
